#

example usage:

```python
from vesicle_distance_analysis.structures import VesicleList, Surface

vl = VesicleList()
s = Surface()
vl.fromXMLFile("path_to_your_file.xml")
s.from_model_auto_segment('path_to_your_membrane_segmentation_result.mod')

vl.distance_from_surface(s)
vl.toXMLFile("output_file.xml")

```

A typical xml file for input should be like this, generated from our template match method or DL-based segmentation method:

```xml
<VesicleList pixelSize="0.857">
  <Vesicle vesicleId="1">
    <Type t="vesicle"/>
    <Center X="310.0" Y="794.0" Z="150.0"/>
    <Radius r="15.7526254376"/>
    <Center2D X="310.3748574604908" Y="795.7467248667151" Z="150.0"/>
    <Radius2D r1="15.521375659057883" r2="14.291893409051173"/>
    <Rotation2D phi="0.678329687373"/>
  </Vesicle>
</VesicleList>
```

For membrane segmentation, we recommend you to use our other method: https://github.com/SynET-Bilab/SegSynMembrane